<br>
So, the container is NO DROP but not NO RENT.<br>
<br>
With the full loot being on him, this means farming. Sigh, they improve things only to ruin them again by a couple of bad choices.<br>
<br>
Ok, he spawns faster now, due to the fact he is not linked to Nagafan.<br>
<br>
But with all the facts now available, this change has actually made the quest harder not easier, as at first it looked. First there is the fact there are now TWO things on long spawn timers to camp, not one. Second, we have farmers to contend with. Third, it will STILL end up being an FFA/greed race, and not a triggerable finale like many other epics. And fourth, clerics who are not even at this point in the epic taking these kills from those who are (though I can see 'last piece' being used as a criteria in cleric epic raids now, like in other epics).<br>
<br>
The only other positive points are, firstly, failing on him doesn't mean re-starting the epic, and secondly, the random 1-3 day timer means he will be up more often.<br>
<br>
Sigh. Opportunity lost to actually make the quest more fun and less unpleasent.<br>
<br>
Ho hum. Let's see how it works.<br>
