</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/26/02 4:00:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=300.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Change to Cleric Epic Quest</span><hr size=1> You are sitting in the throne, in the King room, the cooling corpse of the evil Tranix evidence to your successful adventure. But, uninterested, you get up and walk down the steps into the ante chamber directly infront of you. There is a table and a large chair in there. There were two rather mean looking giants in there before, but you and you colleagues had already sent them to the pits of whatever hell they worshipped. You click on the portcullis, and is clanks and clambers its way up for you, and you pass beneath it.<br>
<br>
You look around. To your right is a fissure containing steaming red hot lava, running away into the distance. To your left, the same, except when your eye follows it, you see it bends to the right around a corner. Ahead of you, is a path, that allows you to move only a few steps, then there is a wall of stone, forcing you to turn left down a slope. Move forward, and as you walk down this ramp, the lava running parallel alongside you on the left gets closer, as the ramp gets lower.<br>
<br>
Then you stop, halfway down that ramp as you are descending, and turn to your left. Looking over the fissure, there is a ledge on the other side of the lava-filled divide, partly obscured by the hot and noxious vapours rising from the bright red molten earth. On the ledge, you can make out the figure of a man, in a bright red robe!<br>
<br>
There is that evil missionary you seek. Give him your Shimmering Pearl, and he is forced to release to you the Swirling Pearl, and is thereby driven back to his void.<br>
<br>
(It is easier to describe more accurately coming from the King room; in practice of course, you have no need to go there, nor indeed fight a single giant, as long as you are careful not to get in range of those in the ante chamber, as I did the first time I was wandering around there *smile*).<br>
<br>
